    "media:imagetext": "TWA-Trans World Airlines, Inc.\nBoeing 707-331C\nTWA was the first airline to operate Boeing 707s in an all\nservice\nDecember\n1983 between sin Francis Los Angeles. Chicago a d\nNew York. Called \"C-Jets\" by the carrier, a total of 18 flew in\nTWA colors. A portion of the fleet was rotated between\ncargo and passenger service, the balance being non-conver-\ntible and used exclusively for freight. TWA retired all of its\nC-Jets as wide-body aircraft with increased cargo capacity\ncame on-line.\nPublished by Aviation World, Inc., P.O. Box 188, Bethel, Conn. 06801 U.S.A.\nB-031\n81554-D\npost card\nN5773T c/n 19214\n2002.113.481",
